Headed out west'?

15
00:05:21.771 --> 00:05:24.115
East.

16
00:05:26.076 --> 00:05:28.078
Away from...

17
00:05:29.045 --> 00:05:30.279
Yeah.

18
00:05:30.280 --> 00:05:33.249
He's probably reading
my note about now.


19
00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:36.051
"By the time I get to Phoenix"?

20
00:05:36.052 --> 00:05:38.089
More or less.

21
00:05:39.689 --> 00:05:41.223
Nice place you got.

22
00:05:41.224 --> 00:05:43.135
You're kidding, right'?

23
00:05:44.794 --> 00:05:47.900
Oh, no, no.
First one's on me.


24
00:05:48.765 --> 00:05:50.244
Thanks.

25
00:05:54.137 --> 00:05:56.583
You okay?

26
00:05:58.742 --> 00:06:02.019
I could really use a shower.

27
00:06:02.178 --> 00:06:07.178
I'd rather not use one
of the rooms right now, but...


28
00:06:09.986 --> 00:06:11.887
Good morning.

29
00:06:13.723 --> 00:06:15.725
Good morning.

30
00:06:23.867 --> 00:06:25.601
Sleep okay?

31
00:06:25.602 --> 00:06:27.582
I slept fine.

32
00:06:28.538 --> 00:06:29.983
Eggs?

33
00:06:33.910 --> 00:06:36.845
You know, why don't you
use my shower.


34
00:06:36.846 --> 00:06:39.281
Soap's nicer than in the rooms.

35
00:06:39.282 --> 00:06:42.217
Make your skin pretty.

36
00:06:42.218 --> 00:06:43.852
Prettier.

37
00:07:17.554 --> 00:07:19.591
This your car?

38
00:07:20.824 --> 00:07:23.192
Can't drive like that.
Tire's flat.


39
00:07:23.193 --> 00:07:25.160
It was driving fine last night.

40
00:07:25.161 --> 00:07:28.063
Well, probably was a slow leak.

41
00:07:28.064 --> 00:07:29.798
Got a spare'?

42
00:07:29.799 --> 00:07:31.300
That was my spare.

43
00:07:31.301 --> 00:07:34.908
Well, miss, lucky I'm here.

44
00:07:51.955 --> 00:07:53.856
Where you headed'?

45
00:07:53.857 --> 00:07:54.990
Twin Cities.

46
00:07:54.991 --> 00:07:57.292
Taking the back roads, huh?
Yeah.


47
00:07:57.293 --> 00:08:00.996
I always feel like the semis are
gonna drive me off the freeway.


48
00:08:00.997 --> 00:08:05.100
You spend any time in Flagstaff?
Passed through.


49
00:08:05.101 --> 00:08:08.137
Seems like a nice town.

50
00:08:08.138 --> 00:08:10.806
On the surface maybe.

51
00:08:10.807 --> 00:08:13.842
Most towns seem nice
on the surface.


52
00:08:13.843 --> 00:08:16.245
In the day, on Main Street.

53
00:08:16.246 --> 00:08:20.115
But at night,
in the bars, motel rooms,


54
00:08:20.116 --> 00:08:23.097
it's a whole nother story.

55
00:08:26.856 --> 00:08:28.096
Yeah.

56
00:08:28.691 --> 00:08:33.003
The nicer the town,
the dirtier the crime.


57
00:08:34.064 --> 00:08:36.203
Spousal abuse.

58
00:08:36.599 --> 00:08:37.733
Molestation.

59
00:08:37.734 --> 00:08:41.570
Drugs. Prostitution. Murder.
Every town's got 'em.


60
00:08:41.571 --> 00:08:44.279
Everyone's guilty of something.

61
00:08:46.943 --> 00:08:49.011
Not a nail after all.

62
00:08:49.012 --> 00:08:51.013
Looks like
your tire got screwed.


63
00:08:59.756 --> 00:09:01.890
Surprised to see you here.

64
00:09:01.891 --> 00:09:05.294
On my way home from Flagstaff.
Long night.


65
00:09:05.295 --> 00:09:05.994
Flagstaff?

66
00:09:05.995 --> 00:09:09.164
Yeah, they wanted
all hands on deck.


67
00:09:09.165 --> 00:09:10.265
Gruesome scene.

68
00:09:10.266 --> 00:09:14.002
You'll hear about it on the
evening news, I'm sure. Mm-hmm.


69
00:09:14.003 --> 00:09:16.839
You mind fetching
Officer Gault some coffee?


70
00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:19.708
Sure. To-go cups
are in the back.


71
00:09:19.709 --> 00:09:23.145
Well, that's my name, Miss...
Laine.


72
00:09:23.146 --> 00:09:27.151
Laine. I'd like it
light and sweet.


73
00:09:53.543 --> 00:09:56.145
You find everything
you're looking for'?


74
00:09:56.146 --> 00:09:57.913
Yeah, I think so.

75
00:09:57.914 --> 00:09:59.181
This place is a dive.

76
00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:03.085
There's plenty of nicer
motels off the freeway.


77
00:10:03.086 --> 00:10:06.158
Maybe I don't like the freeway.

78
00:10:09.659 --> 00:10:11.126
Here you go.

79
00:10:11.127 --> 00:10:13.073
Thanks.

80
00:10:14.964 --> 00:10:16.999
Sweet, but not too sweet.

81
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:18.901
Just the way I like it.
This one's a keeper.


82
00:10:18.902 --> 00:10:23.044
Officer Gault.
Are you there'? Hold on a minute.


83
00:10:24.174 --> 00:10:27.951
How about it'?
How about what'?


84
00:10:29.712 --> 00:10:32.352
Hey, gotta run.
Just need to finish the air.


85
00:10:32.582 --> 00:10:35.317
But it should hold up till
you get where you're going.


86
00:10:35.318 --> 00:10:38.697
Thank you.
My pleasure.


87
00:10:41.791 --> 00:10:43.361
How about staying on?

88
00:10:43.593 --> 00:10:45.928
This place could use
a fresh face.


89
00:10:45.929 --> 00:10:48.000
Free room and board.

90
00:10:48.131 --> 00:10:52.367
I would, um, but my mother's
expecting me up in Minneapolis.


91
00:10:52.368 --> 00:10:55.872
Suit yourself.

92
00:10:57.173 --> 00:10:59.107
Luanne.

93
00:10:59.108 --> 00:11:01.777
I sure would appreciate
a room though.


94
00:11:01.778 --> 00:11:03.979
- Just for the night?
- You can have 3.


95
00:11:03.980 --> 00:11:08.684
But if I get any paying customers,
you're gonna need to clear out.


96
00:11:08.685 --> 00:11:10.255
Okay.

97
00:12:04.674 --> 00:12:08.744
- Flynn, baby, you better be waiting
for me. - Indeed I am, my darling.


98
00:12:08.745 --> 00:12:13.181
I just thought my momentum might
help get you out the door.


99
00:12:13.182 --> 00:12:15.219
Christ.

100
00:12:20.223 --> 00:12:24.296
This dump is deserted.
What did I tell you'?


101
00:12:25.194 --> 00:12:26.728
But I love my diamonds.

102
00:12:26.729 --> 00:12:30.198
You need to wear them
while eating a cheeseburger'?


103
00:12:30.199 --> 00:12:33.835
They don't have steak'?
Gloria, please.


104
00:12:33.836 --> 00:12:36.772
Kidding.
Okay, okay.


105
00:12:36.773 --> 00:12:39.652
Ooh, Jesus Christ.

106
00:14:04.193 --> 00:14:06.298
Piece of junk!

107
00:14:10.199 --> 00:14:13.669
Gloria, open the door.

108
00:14:15.872 --> 00:14:18.106
Will you take that out
to the car for me'?


109
00:14:18.107 --> 00:14:21.143
Gloria, you're not leaving.
The hell I'm not!


110
00:14:21.144 --> 00:14:25.080
- And where will you go'?
- The closest hotel.


111
00:14:25.081 --> 00:14:27.082
Don't be unreasonable.

112
00:14:27.083 --> 00:14:31.086
Did you hear the way
she was talking to me'?


113
00:14:31.087 --> 00:14:32.087
And that place.

114
00:14:32.088 --> 00:14:35.924
Ten minutes in there, and I feel
like there's grease all over me.


115
00:14:35.925 --> 00:14:37.993
And what about your brother?

116
00:14:37.994 --> 00:14:40.634
Eddie can visit me at the hotel.

117
00:14:40.963 --> 00:14:43.098
Where's my jacket'?

118
00:14:43.099 --> 00:14:44.332
Gloria, please.

119
00:14:44.333 --> 00:14:48.804
Have you forgotten the
reason as to why we are here'?


120
00:14:48.805 --> 00:14:51.006
I have not.
Then for God's sake,


121
00:14:51.007 --> 00:14:54.079
will you please try
and be sensible?


122
00:14:54.310 --> 00:14:55.210
Look, after tomorrow night,

123
00:14:55.211 --> 00:15:00.211
we're not going to have to worry
about money for a very long time.


124
00:15:00.683 --> 00:15:03.852
Gloria, Mr. Dunbar
was good to us.


125
00:15:03.853 --> 00:15:05.833
Two big ones.

126
00:15:08.324 --> 00:15:10.926
So tomorrow night we leave'?

127
00:15:10.927 --> 00:15:12.531
Yes.

128
00:15:12.829 --> 00:15:15.664
After they make
the drop-off.


129
00:15:15.665 --> 00:15:16.998
Okay?

130
00:15:16.999 --> 00:15:18.300
Oh, come on.

131
00:15:18.301 --> 00:15:23.301
Darling, why don't you take
one of your little pills


132
00:15:24.140 --> 00:15:26.746
and get ready for bed?

133
00:15:29.912 --> 00:15:31.780
Where are your pills?

134
00:15:31.781 --> 00:15:34.022
Should be in there.

135
00:15:39.155 --> 00:15:41.156
Well,
I don't see them.


136
00:15:41.157 --> 00:15:44.764
There's a new bottle
in the bathroom.


137
00:15:49.131 --> 00:15:50.799
Here, darling.

138
00:15:50.800 --> 00:15:53.835
I never wanna come back
to this rotten place.


139
00:15:53.836 --> 00:15:55.873
Of course not.

140
00:16:07.049 --> 00:16:12.049
♪ Will you come with me,
my Phyllis dear ♪


141
00:16:12.655 --> 00:16:16.626
♪ To yon blue
mountain high'? ♪


142
00:16:16.792 --> 00:16:21.263
♪ Where the blossoms
smell the sweetest ♪


143
00:16:21.264 --> 00:16:25.542
♪ Please come
with me tonight ♪


144
00:16:27.603 --> 00:16:30.812
♪ Wait for the wagon ♪

145
00:16:31.707 --> 00:16:35.849
♪ Wait for the wagon ♪

146
00:16:36.245 --> 00:16:39.247
♪ Wait for the wagon ♪

147
00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:44.960
♪ And we'll all
take a ride ♪


148
00:18:42.805 --> 00:18:45.945
- Good morning.
- Morning.


149
00:18:51.814 --> 00:18:55.318
I slept very well last night.
Happy to hear.


150
00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:58.687
- I woke up this morning, and I was thinking...
- It's too late.


151
00:18:58.688 --> 00:19:01.828
I've changed my mind.
I don't need you anymore.


152
00:19:04.593 --> 00:19:05.927
I really do need a job.

153
00:19:05.928 --> 00:19:08.063
Then why did you turn it down'?

154
00:19:08.064 --> 00:19:11.602
See, that's why
you sleep in a car.


155
00:19:15.671 --> 00:19:16.805
Are you going
to order something?


156
00:19:16.806 --> 00:19:21.516
Because if you're not, we do
reserve the stools for customers.


157
00:19:22.645 --> 00:19:25.580
Well'?
I'm sorry, Luanne.


158
00:19:25.581 --> 00:19:27.652
I was wrong.

159
00:19:27.883 --> 00:19:30.785
I was hurting
and... and tired.


160
00:19:30.786 --> 00:19:34.089
I couldn't think past
getting some rest.


161
00:19:34.090 --> 00:19:38.732
It was very kind of you to
make the offer. I'll say.


162
00:19:40.996 --> 00:19:41.996
Please.

163
00:19:41.997 --> 00:19:46.234
I'm afraid if I don't have
something to cling to right now,


164
00:19:46.235 --> 00:19:49.037
I'll run back to him
all over again.


165
00:19:49.038 --> 00:19:52.874
You're not missing him,
are you'?


166
00:19:52.875 --> 00:19:55.253
It's a vicious cycle.

167
00:19:55.845 --> 00:19:59.581
What about your mother
in Minneapolis?


168
00:19:59.582 --> 00:20:03.118
To be honest,
she doesn't have much.


169
00:20:03.119 --> 00:20:04.886
She drinks.

170
00:20:04.887 --> 00:20:08.130
I suppose I'll just be a burden.

171
00:20:13.295 --> 00:20:17.141
You sure have an odd way
of showing gratitude.


172
00:20:22.605 --> 00:20:25.273
Is that the blouse
you wore yesterday'?


173
00:20:25.274 --> 00:20:27.742
Yeah. I washed it
in the sink.


174
00:20:27.743 --> 00:20:29.978
Well, we'll have to do
something about that.


175
00:20:29.979 --> 00:20:33.324
Where should I start'?
Well...


176
00:20:52.701 --> 00:20:54.302
Who put the noose
around your neck'?


177
00:20:54.303 --> 00:20:57.205
Hey, goddamn it, Lee!
Leave her alone.


178
00:20:57.206 --> 00:20:59.345
She's a good kid.

179
00:21:05.114 --> 00:21:07.015
- Good morning.
- Morning.


180
00:21:09.318 --> 00:21:11.653
Hi. Would you like
some coffee?


181
00:21:11.654 --> 00:21:16.194
If you're pouring, I shall
drink whatever you've got.


182
00:21:21.330 --> 00:21:22.997
Good morning.

183
00:21:22.998 --> 00:21:25.035
Morning.

184
00:21:26.001 --> 00:21:27.268
On vacation'?

185
00:21:27.269 --> 00:21:29.337
Headed for Palm Springs.

186
00:21:29.338 --> 00:21:32.707
My wife likes to think
that she can golf.


187
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:34.976
Can't she'?
She can swing.


188
00:21:34.977 --> 00:21:37.245
Can't hit the ball,
but she can swing.


189
00:21:37.246 --> 00:21:40.114
Put on a fresh pot,
will ya, doll'?


190
00:21:40.115 --> 00:21:44.118
Oh. I should probably get one
of those to go, for the wife.


191
00:21:44.119 --> 00:21:45.687
She has a tough time
falling asleep,


192
00:21:45.688 --> 00:21:50.091
but once she goes down,
a cadaver is easier to wake up.


193
00:21:50.092 --> 00:21:52.368
And how long will you
stay in Palm Springs?


194
00:21:52.595 --> 00:21:54.896
Shouldn't you be scrubbing
a toilet or something'?


195
00:21:59.368 --> 00:22:02.770
- Well, look who stayed.
- Good morning.


196
00:22:02.771 --> 00:22:07.141
I was driving by and saw that Nova
still out there. I had a hunch.


197
00:22:07.142 --> 00:22:11.246
Well, I best check on the wife.

198
00:22:11.247 --> 00:22:14.849
Oh, hey, mister,
do I know you from somewhere?


199
00:22:14.850 --> 00:22:18.853
Excuse me. Didn't you want a
to-go cup for your wife'?


200
00:22:18.854 --> 00:22:21.189
Oh, yes. Thank you.

201
00:22:21.190 --> 00:22:23.725
They took 'em!

202
00:22:23.726 --> 00:22:24.826
- The diamonds!
- What'?


203
00:22:24.827 --> 00:22:26.794
They took my diamond necklace!

204
00:22:26.795 --> 00:22:29.631
Now, sweetie, will you
try and calm down?


205
00:22:29.632 --> 00:22:30.732
Oh, thank God, Officer.

206
00:22:30.733 --> 00:22:33.601
Someone broke into my room
and stole my diamond necklace.


207
00:22:33.602 --> 00:22:36.704
Officer, my wife
is obviously mistaken.


208
00:22:36.705 --> 00:22:38.339
I am not mistaken.

209
00:22:38.340 --> 00:22:40.341
Don't you call me mistaken!

210
00:22:40.342 --> 00:22:45.052
I always put it in the side
pocket of my suitcase.


211
00:22:46.148 --> 00:22:48.182
You! I bet you know
where they are!


212
00:22:48.183 --> 00:22:51.953
I suggest you listen to
your husband and calm down.


213
00:22:51.954 --> 00:22:55.323
Now, Officer, I'm dreadfully sorry
that you've been pulled into this.


214
00:22:55.324 --> 00:22:58.726
- He's trying to help!
- But this is the third time this week


215
00:22:58.727 --> 00:23:01.362
that my wife has misplaced
her zirconia necklace.


216
00:23:01.363 --> 00:23:03.798
She's always worried that
someone's going to steal it,


217
00:23:03.799 --> 00:23:06.100
so she hides it so well
that she can't find it.


218
00:23:06.101 --> 00:23:08.236
I most certainly did not hide it!
And besides...


219
00:23:08.237 --> 00:23:11.673
No, darling, why don't you and
I just go search the room'?


220
00:23:11.674 --> 00:23:13.314
Yeah, maybe you should go
and double-check


221
00:23:13.542 --> 00:23:17.012
before you trouble
the officer any further.


222
00:23:23.953 --> 00:23:25.591
Okay.

223
00:23:25.854 --> 00:23:28.990
But I did not hide it.
Come on, darling.


224
00:23:28.991 --> 00:23:35.203
And if I don't find it, I'll
bring in the whole damn force!


225
00:23:35.631 --> 00:23:37.198
Of course you will, darling.
Come on.


226
00:23:37.199 --> 00:23:39.801
So, you're still
on that Flagstaff case'?


227
00:23:39.802 --> 00:23:44.772
Between that and the Dunbar
heist, our hands are full.


228
00:23:44.773 --> 00:23:46.941
We're making progress.

229
00:23:46.942 --> 00:23:48.943
Hey. Join me outside
for a smoke'?


230
00:23:48.944 --> 00:23:52.213
Wish I could,
but I'm on the clock.


231
00:23:52.214 --> 00:23:54.660
Go ahead.

232
00:23:57.753 --> 00:24:01.756
Must have been a real good
reason made you stay.


233
00:24:01.757 --> 00:24:03.791
Needed a job.
Got one.


234
00:24:03.792 --> 00:24:04.359
Mmm.

235
00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:07.729
I know a girl in a hurry
when I see one.


236
00:24:07.730 --> 00:24:09.030
Uh, found it!

237
00:24:09.031 --> 00:24:10.765
Under the mattress, of course!

238
00:24:10.766 --> 00:24:14.543
Thanks so much for your help!

239
00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:20.074
I should get back to work.

240
00:24:20.075 --> 00:24:23.211
You don't need to be coy with me.
I'm not.


241
00:24:23.212 --> 00:24:24.912
Here's what I'm thinking.

242
00:24:24.913 --> 00:24:26.080
9:00 my shift ends.

243
00:24:26.081 --> 00:24:30.952
Pick you up, bring you back to my house.
I'll throw some rib eye on the grill.


244
00:24:30.953 --> 00:24:35.231
We'll drink some wine
and discuss our situation.


245
00:24:35.891 --> 00:24:38.337
You're barking up
the wrong tree, Officer.


246
00:24:38.560 --> 00:24:39.894
You're not serious.

247
00:24:39.895 --> 00:24:43.934
Your kind will
never do it for me.


248
00:24:44.967 --> 00:24:47.709
Better if you left me alone.

249
00:24:47.870 --> 00:24:53.843
Desert's a lonely place, so don't
come scratching at my door.


250
00:25:30.012 --> 00:25:32.219
Nice to see you too, pops.

251
00:25:35.317 --> 00:25:37.752
Loraine, right?
Luanne.


252
00:25:37.753 --> 00:25:42.156
Yeah. Well, I'm gonna need the
