01:05:22.569 --> 01:05:23.569
He could be anywhere by now.

762
01:05:23.570 --> 01:05:28.173
Stop at the first gas station,
see if somebody spotted him.


763
01:05:28.174 --> 01:05:31.519
How are we
going to find him'?


764
01:05:32.078 --> 01:05:33.614
Gloria?

765
01:05:33.813 --> 01:05:36.949
- I don't know where he is.
- Take a guess.


766
01:05:36.950 --> 01:05:39.151
I don't know!

767
01:05:39.152 --> 01:05:42.955
- Why would he do this'?
- Ask him when we find him.


768
01:05:42.956 --> 01:05:45.257
Right now I just
wanna know where he is,


769
01:05:45.258 --> 01:05:48.296
so think, damn it, think!

770
01:05:52.165 --> 01:05:56.079
What is it'? There's
something up ahead.


771
01:06:03.309 --> 01:06:06.602
Flynn. Don't let him!
Don't let him, Flynn!


772
01:06:06.627 --> 01:06:07.748
All right.

773
01:06:23.696 --> 01:06:24.997
He left his gun?

774
01:06:24.998 --> 01:06:27.099
Actually, it looks like mine.

775
01:06:27.100 --> 01:06:28.767
Look! There's blood!

776
01:06:28.768 --> 01:06:31.303
There's blood on the road!

777
01:06:31.304 --> 01:06:32.938
Is it Eddie's'?

778
01:06:32.939 --> 01:06:34.106
Does he bleed red'?

779
01:06:34.107 --> 01:06:38.249
Come on, darling. Get in the car.
Just get in the car.


780
01:06:42.682 --> 01:06:44.716
He couldn't have gotten far.

781
01:06:44.717 --> 01:06:47.786
If we find him, will you
let me talk to him'?


782
01:06:47.787 --> 01:06:51.256
- Lee, will you let me talk to him first?
- .Jesus Christ!


783
01:06:51.257 --> 01:06:53.965
Shut the fuck up!

784
01:06:58.898 --> 01:07:02.277
Wait a minute.
What's that?


785
01:07:06.139 --> 01:07:07.914
That's Eddie!

786
01:07:08.942 --> 01:07:10.242
Oh! Eddie!

787
01:07:10.243 --> 01:07:13.845
Oh, my... Oh! Eddie.
Eddie. Eddie.


788
01:07:13.846 --> 01:07:16.748
Eddie!
Why did you do it'?


789
01:07:16.749 --> 01:07:19.718
Eddie, why did you do it'?

790
01:07:19.719 --> 01:07:22.054
You know I wouldn't.

791
01:07:22.055 --> 01:07:23.088
I was gonna...

792
01:07:23.089 --> 01:07:27.128
I don't care why he did it.
Is it all there?


793
01:07:29.028 --> 01:07:31.597
Lee, don't you do this!

794
01:07:31.598 --> 01:07:35.133
He's hurt! Look at him.
He's hurt!


795
01:07:35.134 --> 01:07:36.568
The coffee.

796
01:07:36.569 --> 01:07:40.672
- It was in the coffee.
- I know it was the coffee.


797
01:07:40.673 --> 01:07:42.874
No! You're a beast!
I won't let you do it!


798
01:07:42.875 --> 01:07:46.755
If you want to shoot him,
you'll have to go through me.


799
01:08:20.580 --> 01:08:22.821
Such a tragedy.

800
01:08:35.161 --> 01:08:38.199
Why the hell
did you have to kill her'?


801
01:08:38.665 --> 01:08:41.233
At this pace,
you may well be next.


802
01:08:41.234 --> 01:08:43.669
Now open the trunk.
Why?


803
01:08:43.670 --> 01:08:47.516
This is where you earn
your thousand dollars.


804
01:08:47.640 --> 01:08:50.678
I asked for 2,000.
Open it.


805
01:08:54.080 --> 01:08:55.313
Jesus Christ!

806
01:08:55.314 --> 01:08:57.582
Who the hell is that'?

807
01:08:57.583 --> 01:08:59.685
Eddie did this'?

808
01:08:59.686 --> 01:09:01.996
How?
How do you think'?


809
01:09:02.822 --> 01:09:04.589
Help me with the bodies.

810
01:09:04.590 --> 01:09:06.934
Let's get this done, now!

811
01:09:39.559 --> 01:09:41.971
I'm sorry.

812
01:09:47.700 --> 01:09:49.543
Flynn?

813
01:09:49.802 --> 01:09:52.248
You want me to drive'?

814
01:09:53.039 --> 01:09:55.707
Flynn?

815
01:10:36.048 --> 01:10:39.655
Stop it, Flynn!
Get off of her!


816
01:10:49.228 --> 01:10:52.107
Shoot him!
No.


817
01:10:58.905 --> 01:11:00.942
What a shame.

818
01:11:01.274 --> 01:11:04.118
Goddamn it.

819
01:11:05.378 --> 01:11:08.257
Just get me in the car.

820
01:11:13.886 --> 01:11:18.023
Tell me, what is it
that keeps you up at night?


821
01:11:18.024 --> 01:11:21.827
Luanne, there's a doctor
in New River.


822
01:11:21.828 --> 01:11:24.095
He'll take care of me there.

823
01:11:24.096 --> 01:11:26.898
Those aren't things
to worry about.


824
01:11:26.899 --> 01:11:29.968
Christmas is
right around the corner.


825
01:11:29.969 --> 01:11:31.670
And we're all here.

826
01:11:31.671 --> 01:11:33.238
Luanne, I'm gonna die.

827
01:11:33.239 --> 01:11:35.841
Don't you see'?

828
01:11:35.842 --> 01:11:38.109
There's no time for tears.

829
01:11:38.110 --> 01:11:42.714
Is... is that
from your goddamn movie'?


830
01:11:42.715 --> 01:11:45.958
Goddamn it, Luanne!

831
01:11:47.587 --> 01:11:48.653
Look.

832
01:11:48.654 --> 01:11:53.091
The snow is falling.
I think it's a sign.


833
01:11:53.092 --> 01:11:56.869
Next year will surely be heaven.

834
01:12:07.006 --> 01:12:09.816
Will you be a doll and drive'?

835
01:12:10.676 --> 01:12:12.043
But he's gonna die.

836
01:12:12.044 --> 01:12:15.914
We can't be going to New River.

837
01:12:15.915 --> 01:12:18.122
Not tonight.

838
01:12:23.022 --> 01:12:25.590
You've been such a big help.

839
01:12:25.591 --> 01:12:29.095
I'd hate to have to leave you.

840
01:12:39.171 --> 01:12:43.278
Well, that went better
than expected.


841
01:12:44.310 --> 01:12:46.211
Where are we going?

842
01:12:46.212 --> 01:12:48.214
The Frontier.

843
01:14:21.807 --> 01:14:25.744
I couldn't have done
this without you.


844
01:14:25.745 --> 01:14:31.627
So I want you to have this.

845
01:14:33.719 --> 01:14:36.988
I don't know
how much is in there,


846
01:14:36.989 --> 01:14:39.691
but it should last you a while.

847
01:14:39.692 --> 01:14:41.569
Go ahead.

848
01:14:42.094 --> 01:14:44.963
I don't know what to say.

849
01:14:44.964 --> 01:14:47.035
Thank you.

850
01:14:47.867 --> 01:14:50.101
Oh, you're so young.

851
01:14:50.102 --> 01:14:53.071
I'm gonna teach you
everything I know.


852
01:14:53.072 --> 01:14:56.875
Now, if you wouldn't mind,
go make us some coffee.


853
01:14:56.876 --> 01:15:01.848
I'm gonna round up a few
things before we hit the road.


854
01:15:02.281 --> 01:15:04.916
We don't have much time.

855
01:15:04.917 --> 01:15:06.726
Yeah.

856
01:15:47.293 --> 01:15:49.136
Laine'?

857
01:16:23.762 --> 01:16:26.174
Stop it!

858
01:17:35.935 --> 01:17:41.214
♪ I can't believe you
looked me in the face ♪


859
01:17:43.042 --> 01:17:47.821
♪ Can't believe you would go ♪

860
01:17:49.582 --> 01:17:54.156
♪ All my tears keep on sayin' ♪

861
01:17:56.755 --> 01:18:00.965
♪ I love you so ♪

862
01:18:01.727 --> 01:18:07.700
♪ I'm sorry for all the
times I hurt you ♪


863
01:18:08.867 --> 01:18:14.078
♪ Sorry for all the
times I lied ♪


864
01:18:14.640 --> 01:18:20.818
♪ Give me one more chance
and I'll show you ♪


865
01:18:22.748 --> 01:18:28.164
♪ The devil has died ♪

866
01:18:28.921 --> 01:18:33.995
♪ I can't change
what's happened ♪


867
01:18:34.593 --> 01:18:39.906
♪ Let me try
to ease the pain ♪

868
01:18:42.234 --> 01:18:45.103
♪ Please don't go ♪

869
01:18:45.104 --> 01:18:47.311
♪ I need you so ♪

870
01:18:47.539 --> 01:18:54.115
♪ I know I'm to blame ♪

871
01:18:55.014 --> 01:18:59.793
♪ If my tears cannot stop you ♪

872
01:19:00.886 --> 01:19:02.220
♪ One thing be... ♪

873
01:19:06.925 --> 01:19:09.303
Hold it right there.

874
01:19:21.740 --> 01:19:23.875
Drop the bag.

875
01:19:25.010 --> 01:19:28.583
Kneel.
Hands on your head.


876
01:19:54.073 --> 01:19:56.713
She's dead, isn't she?

877
01:20:08.120 --> 01:20:12.056
Dispatch. This is 62A
requesting backup.


878
01:20:12.057 --> 01:20:13.991
Your 926'?

879
01:20:13.992 --> 01:20:18.162
Frontier Motel.
Old 66. Truxton.


880
01:20:18.163 --> 01:20:20.298
Copy that. The situation'?

881
01:20:22.201 --> 01:20:24.836
We got at least
a half dozen bodies here.


882
01:20:24.837 --> 01:20:28.284
Half a mile down the road,
near a vehicle.


883
01:20:29.141 --> 01:20:32.844
And at least one here
at the motel.


884
01:20:32.845 --> 01:20:34.045
Jesus Christ.

885
01:20:34.046 --> 01:20:37.148
Looks like some of the players
from the Dunbar heist.


886
01:20:37.149 --> 01:20:39.755
Any sign of the money'?

887
01:20:40.953 --> 01:20:45.732
- Is this everything?
- As far as I know.


888
01:20:49.361 --> 01:20:51.662
No sign of the money,

889
01:20:51.663 --> 01:20:54.999
but I'll have backup
search the premises.


890
01:20:55.000 --> 01:20:57.173
Please stand by.

891
01:21:02.975 --> 01:21:06.210
Those people in the trunk...

892
01:21:06.211 --> 01:21:09.090
Eddie couldn't have killed them.

893
01:21:11.250 --> 01:21:13.985
And who are you?

894
01:21:13.986 --> 01:21:16.296
Just a customer.

895
01:21:25.931 --> 01:21:28.733
Picked the wrong motel,
didn't you?


896
01:21:28.734 --> 01:21:32.003
Woke up.
Heard some screaming.


897
01:21:32.004 --> 01:21:34.205
Gunshots down the road.

898
01:21:34.206 --> 01:21:38.313
Stepped out and almost
got yourself killed.


899
01:21:39.678 --> 01:21:42.682
Yeah, that sounds about right.

900
01:21:43.015 --> 01:21:46.851
In a few minutes, a whole lot
of people are gonna be here


901
01:21:46.852 --> 01:21:48.820
to clean up this shithole.

902
01:21:48.821 --> 01:21:54.066
Make sure you're here. They're
gonna ask you some questions.


903
01:21:54.626 --> 01:21:56.828
What am I supposed
to tell them'?


904
01:21:56.829 --> 01:21:59.673
The truth, naturally.

905
01:22:40.906 --> 01:22:43.978
And in Truxton, the
three-week search for those responsible


906
01:22:44.042 --> 01:22:47.211
in the Dunbar armored truck
heist ended in violence today.


907
01:22:47.212 --> 01:22:50.648
Three suspects-John Flynn,
Lee Towers and Eddie King...


908
01:22:50.649 --> 01:22:52.850
Were found dead along Route 66.

909
01:22:52.851 --> 01:22:55.353
The fourth, Luanne
Brice, was found dead


910
01:22:55.354 --> 01:22:56.654
at the local motel she owned.

911
01:22:56.655 --> 01:23:00.258
In a strange turn of events authorities
have also obtained evidence


912
01:23:00.259 --> 01:23:02.827
linking the thieves to the
murder of Jed H. Burnham,


913
01:23:02.828 --> 01:23:06.898
whose body was found earlier
this week at a Flagstaff motel.


914
01:23:06.899 --> 01:23:08.900
Burnham's father, H.W. Burnham,

915
01:23:08.901 --> 01:23:12.069
has commended police for
solving his son's murder.


916
01:23:12.070 --> 01:23:15.950
So far, no money has
been recovered.